description.narrative: (Indonesia): In FY 2015, funds will support innovative investment opportunities to strengthen policy under USAID's primary CDCS focus areas: environment, health, education, human rights and anti-corruption. Partnerships forged with local research institutes, think-tanks and CSOs will continue to play a critical role in achieving numerous objectives under the CDCS. The project will also continue to lend support to strengthening GOI's South-South & Triangular Cooperation (SSTC) Program through analysis and inclusion of civil society, private sector and university stakeholders.Expected results: -Policy research, independent analysis and public consideration of legislation and policies improved. -Evidenced-based approach to policy formulation and implementation in the key areas of health, education, environment, accountability and human rights strengthened.-Participation of civil society, private sector and universities as key stakeholders in SSTC increased.
